Privacy Policy for The Silent Classroom

Effective Date: 03/07/2025
Last Updated: 03/07/2025

1. Introduction
Welcome to The Silent Classroom, a VR serious game designed to enhance ASL learning through immersive interaction. Your privacy is important to us, and this Privacy Policy explains how we handle any information you provide while using our game.
2. Information We Collect
We do not collect, store, or share any personal data from players. The only information we receive is voluntary feedback from users who choose to provide it to help improve the game.
3. How We Use Feedback
Any feedback submitted by players will be used solely for:
•	Enhancing the game experience based on user suggestions.
•	Fixing bugs and improving game performance.
•	Understanding user preferences for future updates.
4. Data Sharing and Security
•	We do not collect gameplay data, hand tracking information, or personal identifiers.
•	Any feedback provided remains confidential and will not be shared with third parties.
•	No personal information is required to play the game.
5. Children's Privacy
The Silent Classroom is designed for educational purposes and does not collect any personal information from players, including children under 13.
6. Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated as needed. Any changes will be reflected with a new "Last Updated" date.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or wish to provide feedback, please contact us at:
Pritony034@gmail.com


